From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Project OS Build Fix <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sat, 31 May 2026 12:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] filan: fix printtime const assignment error

Upstream-Status: Pending

`asctime()` returns a mutable buffer. The local variable must not be const,
because the code strips the trailing newline in-place.

---
 filan.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/filan.c b/filan.c
index dc56e44..70bcf62 100644
--- a/filan.c
+++ b/filan.c
@@ -1056,7 +1056,7 @@ const char *sockaddr_info(const struct sockaddr *sa, union sockaddr_union *sau,
 }

 static int printtime(FILE *outfile, time_t time) {
-   const char *s;
+   char *s;

    if (filan_rawoutput) {
       fprintf(outfile, "\t"F_time, time);
--
